'''人類的性'''是人類體驗或表達满足自身[[性_(生物學)|性]][[本能|本能]]或[[人类性行为|性方面]]有关的行动的方式或整体<ref name="Cavendish">{{cite book|title=Sex and Society, Volume 2|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=978-0-7614-7907-9|year=2010|page=384|access-date=2017-06-21|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YtsxeWE7VD0C&pg=PA384|quote=The term human sexuality broadly refers to how people experience and express themselves as sexual beings.|archive-date=2018-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224231840/https://books.google.com/books?id=YtsxeWE7VD0C&pg=PA384|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Ferrante">{{cite book|author=Joan Ferrante|title=Sociology: A Global Perspective|publisher=Cengage Learning|isbn=978-1-285-74646-3|year=2014|page=207|access-date=2017-06-21|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Au4bCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA207|quote=Sexuality encompasses all the ways people experience and express themselves as sexual beings.|archive-date=2018-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224231841/https://books.google.com/books?id=Au4bCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA207|dead-url=no}}</ref>。它牽涉到人類在[[生物学|生物上]]、[[情色性|情色上]]、[[身體親密|身體上]]、[[情感親密|情感上]]、[[社交|社會上]]和[[靈性|宗教上/精神上]]的感受或行為<ref name="S. Greenberg">{{cite book|first1=Jerrold S.|last1=Greenberg|first2=Clint E.|last2=Bruess|first3=Sara B.|last3=Oswalt|title=Exploring the Dimensions of Human Sexuality|publisher=Jones & Bartlett Publishers|isbn=978-1-284-08154-1|year=2016|pages=4–10|access-date=2017-06-21|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8iarCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA4|quote=Human sexuality is a part of your total personality. It involves the interrelationship of biological, psychological, and sociocultural dimensions. [...] It is the total of our physical, emotional, and spiritual responses, thoughts, and feelings.|archive-date=2018-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224231839/https://books.google.com/books?id=8iarCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA4|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Bolin">{{cite book|first1=Anne |last1=Bolin |first2=Patricia |last2=Whelehan|title=Human Sexuality: Biological, Psychological, and Cultural Perspectives|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-7890-2671-2|year=2009|pages=32–42|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qrPHYok19v8C&pg=PA32}}</ref>。由於其背後意義會隨著時間及歷史背景而改變，故難以精確定義之<ref name="Bolin"/>。身體或生物上的性主要牽涉到[[人類繁殖|人類的繁殖功能]]，乃至[[人类性反应周期|人类性反应周期]]<ref name="S. Greenberg"/><ref name="Bolin"/>。

[[性取向|性取向]]是指對於同性或異性產生性興趣的特定模式<ref name="AmPsycholAssn-whatis">{{cite web |title=Sexual orientation, homosexuality and bisexuality |publisher=[[美国心理学会|American Psychological Association]] |access-date=2013-08-10 |url=http://www.apa.org/helpcenter/sexual-orientation.aspx |archive-date=2013-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130808032050/http://www.apa.org/helpcenter/sexual-orientation.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref>。身體和情感上的性包含人與人之間的紐帶，其可透過深如似海般的感情，或因[[浪漫關係|愛]]、信任、關懷等情感而生的行為來表達。人類社會會對某人的性產生一定影響，故此性也是一門關乎社會的事。宗教上/精神上的性則關乎某人在精神上跟他人的聯繫。性亦對哲學、法律、政治、文化、[[伦理学|伦理]][[道德|道德]]、宗教產生一定影響，反之亦然<ref name="S. Greenberg"/><ref name="Bolin"/>。

在大多社會中，人們對性行為的興趣一般會在[[青春期|青春期]]期間増加<ref>Carlson, Neil R. and C. Donald Heth. "Psychology: the Science of Behaviour." 4th Edition. Toronto: Pearson Canada Inc., 2007. 684.</ref>。儘管目前沒有一套有關性取向成因的理論得到科學界廣泛支持，但與社會性因子相比，生物性因子得到更多的證據支持，對於男性的情況而言更是如此<ref name=Bailey16>{{cite journal|last1=Bailey|first1=J. Michael|last2=Vasey|first2=Paul|last3=Diamond|first3=Lisa|last4=Breedlove|first4=S. Marc|last5=Vilain|first5=Eric|last6=Epprecht|first6=Marc|title=Sexual Orientation, Controversy, and Science|journal=Psychological Science in the Public Interest|date=2016|volume=17|issue=2|pages=45–101|doi=10.1177/1529100616637616|pmid=27113562|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/301639075|access-date=2021-01-03|archive-date=2020-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611031054/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/301639075|dead-url=no}}</ref>。跨文化研究亦支持性取向的生物性因子——不同文化的同性戀人口比例沒有太大差異<ref name=LeVay>{{cite book |last=LeVay |first=Simon |date=2017 |title=Gay, Straight, and the Reason Why: The Science of Sexual Orientation |page=19 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HmQFFfa03nkC |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=9780199752966 |access-date=2021-01-03 |archive-date=2020-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022014657/https://books.google.com/books?id=HmQFFfa03nkC |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Balthazart>{{cite book |last=Balthazart |first=Jacques |date=2012 |title=The Biology of Homosexuality |pages=13–14 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3fjGjlcVINkC |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=9780199838820 |access-date=2021-01-03 |archive-date=2021-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126132532/https://books.google.com/books?id=3fjGjlcVINkC |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

演化學和[[社會學習理論|社會學習理論]]能提供了一個嶄新的視角去看待人類的性行為、繁殖、繁殖策略<ref>''Sexual Strategies Theory: An Evolutionary Perspective on Human Mating'' by David M. Buss and David P. Schmitt</ref>。性的社會文化層面則牽涉到人類性史的發展和[[宗教與性|宗教跟性的關係]]。研究者視一些文化為[[性压抑|性压抑]]的。性研究亦會探討[[个体|個人]]在社會中的身份認同、[[性傳染病|性傳染病]]、[[生育控制|生育控制]]方法。
